</paragraph>
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBFFFE56DC2FE3EFEBCAAD4" blockId="27.[178,1085,418,470]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBFFFE56F58FE3FFD17AAB5" box="[552,642,418,439]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">fasciatus</emphasis>
, is a Latin noun. I refer to the fascia on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
